{"post-82963": {"user": "Admin", "user_num": 1, "timestamp": "1527814375000", "message": "Creating New Characters and Accounts\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0To create an account for the first time, click on the button marked   in the top right, directly below the banner. It will prompt you for your email and other information. This is your global (proboards) account, which represents you as a player. It is tied to your email address and hosts all of your characters.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0When it asks for a 'username,' put in the username you would like your first character to have. Note that usernames and display names are not the same; display names can be changed, usernames cannot.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0After successfully creating an account, you will now have access to the  button on the top navigation list; clicking it will take you to the character's profile. Part of creating a character is filling in their profile with descriptions and biographical information.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0To start, click on the  button, and under the \"Personal\" tab, fill in your character sheet. There are no requirements for character sheets. You may put as much or as little as you would like, but we suggest you at least describe the character's appearance.Make sure to save your changes when you\u2019re finished!You may not create accounts to represent gods or spell effects, and excessively large characters are highly discouraged. There are no other restrictions on character creation.You can switch rapidly between your characters by using this button on the toolbar in the bottom-right corner of your screen:For more on creating characters, refer to this thread: Naoki's Style Guide", "link_list": ["https://login.proboards.com/register/6046952", "http://thefantasysandbox.boards.net/user/", "https://login.proboards.com/select/login/6046952", "http://thefantasysandbox.boards.net/thread/2293/naokis-style-guide"], "image_list": ["http://i.imgur.com/tvGCsnd.png", "https://i.imgur.com/NOPLXRX.